                    </div>
                    <span>Even though I had a reasonable background in using vb.net, I just couldn't put all the pieces together for ASP.NET when using Microsoft's ASP.net with VB .net (G. Andrew Duthie).  After reading ASP.NET for Dummies, the ASP.NET technology finally started to make sense.  
<br />Now I've been able to return to G. Andrew Duthie's book and get more out of it.  
<br />One negative comment though--even though vb.net still supports much of the old vb6 style programming, the book should have used the .net OOP style throughout.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Excellent Book for Beginners</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
